apache-log4j2 (2.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Team upload.
  * Imported Upstream version 2.2.
  * liblog4j2-java.poms:
    - Remove log4j-osgi/pom.xml --ignore
    - Ignore log4j-bom.
    - Add log4j-nosql --has-package-version --java-lib line.
    - Add log4j-web pom.xml.
    - Add log4j2-perf pom.xml.
    - Ignore log4j2-perf for now because it requires Maven 3.
    - Ignore log4j-iostreams.
    - Add log4j2-jul.
  * maven.ignoreRules: Ignore all artifacts which make the build FTBFS,
    including maven-failsafe-plugin, woodstox-core-asl, json-unit,
    activemq-broker.
  * debian/control:
    - Declare compliance with Debian Policy 3.9.6.
    - Switch Vcs-Browser field to cgit.
    - Add libmaven-source-plugin-java to Build-Depends-Indep.
    - Add libcommons-lang3-java to Build-Depends-Indep.
    - Add libjackson2-dataformat-yaml to Build-Depends-Indep.
    - Add libjackson2-dataformat-xml-java to Build-Depends-Indep.
    - Add jackson-module-jaxb-annotations to Build-Depends-Indep.
    - Add libjboss-jms-api-java to Build-Depends-Indep.
  * Update maven.rules due to additional build-dependencies.

  [ Emmanuel Bourg ]
  * debian/watch: Watch the release tags on Github

